      "solution": "# Solution is here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1823058/how-to-print-number-with-commas-as-thousands-separators\nn = int(input())\ndef group(number):\n    s = '%d' % number\n    groups = []\n    while s and s[-1].isdigit():\n        groups.append(s[-3:])\n        s = s[:-3]\n    return s + ','.join(reversed(groups))\nprint(group(n))",
